For example, only 16 of the 34 states have passed laws requiring the presentation of a photo ID.
However, the new rules introduced in 2012 will undoubtedly make it more difficult to exercise the right to vote.
The democratic critics denounce the party political nature of the laws adopted and see them as a clear goal of influencing the results in the states that are decisive for 2012.
A 2011 report by the Brennan Center shows that those states that have passed these laws constitute 171 of the 270 votes needed in the electoral panel to win the presidency.
It is too early to confirm with certainty that these changes to legislation on the electoral system will have a significant impact on the outcome of the 2012 presidential elections.
But one thing is certain: these new rules will have a negative impact on voter turnout.
