Although several Hamas leaders are killed and the 1.7 million inhabitants of the Gaza Strip are cremated in one of the most desolate and densely populated corners of the planet, Israel has not yet succeeded in destroying Hamas.
Indeed, Hamas is gaining ground in the West Bank, controlled by the rival, moderate Palestinian group Fatah.
And Hamas leaders could conclude that they have time on their side.
Just as Islamists gained influence in the Arab world, Hamas has been able to draw powerful and rich friends to its side.
