Foreign Arab nations should also move Hamas and Fatah to an agreement.
This would do more for the creation of a Palestinian state than with the forthcoming request for UN observer status.
Obama, too, must help to persuade Israel to negotiate.
During his first term, he failed to present his own peace plan.
Far away in the white house, it seems that he is equally opposed to participation.
But that is a regrettable, short-sighted perspective.
The United States has a significant interest in a stable Middle East.
