And if Sweden interrogated Mr Assange at the Ecuadorian Embassy in London or via Skype, as Swedish jurisprudence allows and has done in other cases, the problem is resolved.
Correa took the opportunity to confirm himself as a defender of freedom of the press and said that what he did not tolerate were "the mediocrity, the evil intention and the lie that invalidated freedom of expression."
